{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"25b8d2b8-9a43-4cf7-b999-a0d277e124f4","content":"Your project is already set up. Run your tests in hot-reload mode with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts a watch-style session. When you save changes to your test or source files, the test runner automatically re-executes the affected tests **without a full rebuild**. The workflow is:\n\n1. Run `dotnet test --hotreload`\n2. See which tests fail\n3. Edit your code/tests in another terminal\n4. Save — tests re-run automatically\n5. Repeat until green\n\nIt leverages .NET's hot reload infrastructure so only the changed methods are patched in-place, giving you a much faster feedback loop than `dotnet test` from scratch each time.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2f755e75-b776-4529-8c39-4ff6019a5cee","outputTokens":163,"requestId":"E3CC:2B8350:6C79FC:7C76EC:6A052921"},"id":"38ffad49-73d2-485c-a98f-bf75b7cc37d8","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:45:11.573Z","parentId":"0844f6a1-83c5-4196-b1d7-c9e23234df95"}
